::h2 align=left break=column Problem 136

::prb sz=13 ca="Problem 136"

Where does White play to live?

::h3 break=page Answer 136

::fig sz=13 to=1 ca="Correct Answer"

White 1 is the vital point. White has two distinct eyes and cannot be killed.

::dia sz=13 mv=F7F6 ca="Wrong Answer"

If White captures a stone with 1, Black 2 leaves White with only one real eye, so he is dead.


::go pl=b
ab=D18E18H18F17G17H17
aw=E19H19F18G18J18C17D17E17J17
mv=G19F19D19

::h2 align=left break=column Problem 207

::prb ca="Problem 207" vw=A13L19

Capture three white stones with the connect-and-capture technique.

::h3 break=page Answer 207

::fig to=3 ca="Correct Answer" vw=A13L19

Black sacrifices a stone with 1, then plays 3. White can’t connect, so he has lost four stones.

::dia mv=D19G19 ca="Wrong Answer" vw=A13L19

If Black plays 1 first, he fails. White connects with 2 and his stones are safe.


